Function: albasistoalg
Section: algebras
C-Name: albasistoalg
Prototype: GG
Help: albasistoalg(al,x): transforms the column vector x on the integral
 basis of al into an element of al in algebraic form.

Doc: Given an element \var{x} in the central simple algebra \var{al} output
 by \tet{alinit}, transforms it to its algebraic representation in \var{al}.
 This is the inverse function of \tet{alalgtobasis}.
 \bprog
 ? A = alinit(nfinit(y^2-5),[2,y]);
 ? z = albasistoalg(A,[0,1,0,0,2,-3,0,0]~);
 ? liftall(z)
 %3 = [(-1/2*y - 2)*x + (-1/4*y + 5/4), -3/4*y + 7/4]~
 ? alalgtobasis(A,z)
 %4 = [0, 1, 0, 0, 2, -3, 0, 0]~
 @eprog
